==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predesignate
<hw>Pre*des"ig*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Logic)</fld>
<def>A term used by Sir William Hamilton to define propositions having
their quantity indicated by a verbal sign; <as>as, <ex>all</ex>,
<ex>none</ex>, etc.</as>; -- contrasted with <xex>preindesignate</xex>,
defining propositions of which the quantity is not so
indicated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predestinarian</ent>⟦br⟧
